messages.content:
You need **Universal Links** (iOS) and **App Links** (Android):

**iOS Universal Links**:
1. Host an `apple-app-site-association` file at `https://yourapp.com/.well-known/apple-app-site-association`:
```json
{
  "applinks": {
    "apps": [],
    "details": [{
      "appID": "TEAM_ID.com.yourapp.app",
      "paths": ["/product/*", "/profile/*"]
    }]
  }
}
```
2. Add Associated Domains in Xcode: `applinks:yourapp.com`
3. Handle in app: `application(_:continue:restorationHandler:)`

**Android App Links**:
1. Host a `assetlinks.json` at `https://yourapp.com/.well-known/assetlinks.json`:
```json
[{
  "relation": ["delegate_permission/common.handle_all_urls"],
  "target": {
    "namespace": "android_app",
    "package_name": "com.yourapp.app",
    "sha256_cert_fingerprints": ["your_cert_sha256"]
  }
}]
```
2. Add intent filter in AndroidManifest with `autoVerify="true"`

**For React Native with Expo**:
```javascript
// app.json
"expo": {
  "scheme": "yourapp",
  "ios": { "associatedDomains": ["applinks:yourapp.com"] },
  "android": { "intentFilters": [...] }
}
```

Use Expo Router for handling incoming links — it maps URLs to screens via file-based routing.
